messages.subject: Re: OH! OH! Myers-Briggs
messages.msgSnippet: ... I m an ENFJ, oddly enough (for an unschooler) labeled as The Teacher . Though this part of the definition clarifies it a bit: The Teacher is especially
messages.messageBody:
Tim and Maureen wrote:
>http://www.humanmetrics.com
>
>Take the test people! Let's share! :O)


I'm an ENFJ, oddly enough (for an unschooler) labeled as "The Teacher".
Though this part of the definition clarifies it a bit: "The Teacher is
especially capable of educing or calling forth those inner potentials each
learner possesses. Even as children the Teachers may attract a gathering of
other children ready to follow their lead in play or work. And they lead
without seeming to do so."

I have to admit, the description given fits me pretty well. And I do spend a
lot of time teaching (adults that is). I'm currently a swim and triathlon
coach and have also taught computer programming, skydiving, and other random
things. Interesting.

Blue Skies!
-Robin-

messages.subject: RE: [Unschooling-dotcom] Re: OH! OH! Myers-Briggs
messages.msgSnippet: Thanks for finding that treegodess! I am still INFP: Very expressed Introvert Moderately expressed iNtuitive Moderately expressed Feeler Slightly expressed
messages.messageBody:
Thanks for finding that treegodess!
I am still INFP:

Very expressed Introvert
Moderately expressed iNtuitive
Moderately expressed Feeler
Slightly expressed Perceiver

Same as 20 yrs ago, I wavered near the border between Perception and
judgement. That means my dominant trait leans toward my perception (my
intuition), though my judging trait (my feeling)is vying for attention.

Susan...off to explore that website a bit more
